     <h2>Introduction to the Stock Market</h2>

<p>
The stock market is a platform where shares of companies are bought and sold.
When you invest in stocks, you become a partial owner of businesses and
participate in their growth over time.
</p>

<p>
These transactions take place on regulated stock exchanges.
In India, the two primary exchanges are the
<strong>National Stock Exchange (NSE)</strong> and the
<strong>Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE)</strong>.
</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>NSE:</strong>
    India’s largest exchange by volume, home to the NIFTY 50 index
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>BSE:</strong>
    Asia’s oldest stock exchange, represented by the SENSEX index
  </li>
</ul>

<p>
Market performance is measured using indices.
<strong>NIFTY 50</strong> tracks 50 leading companies on the NSE,
while <strong>SENSEX</strong> tracks 30 established companies on the BSE.
</p>

<p>
Globally, markets are tracked through indices like
<strong>Dow Jones</strong>, <strong>S&P 500</strong>, and <strong>NASDAQ</strong>,
which reflect the performance of major U.S. companies.
</p>

<p>
Each company trades using a unique symbol called a <strong>ticker</strong>,
which helps investors identify and trade stocks on an exchange.
</p>

<p class="text-muted">
Understanding exchanges and indices is the first step before learning
how markets move and how investment decisions are made.
</p>
