    <h2>Technical Analysis</h2>

<p>
Technical analysis focuses on understanding price movement using charts.
Instead of studying the company itself, it analyzes how buyers and sellers
behave in the market.
</p>

<p>
Prices move in patterns, trends, and cycles.
By studying historical price data, traders attempt to identify
potential future movements.
</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Candlestick Charts:</strong>
    Visual representation of price action over time
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Trends:</strong>
    Identifying whether the market is moving up, down, or sideways
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Support & Resistance:</strong>
    Key price levels where buying or selling pressure increases
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Indicators:</strong>
    Tools like Moving Averages and RSI used to confirm trends
  </li>
</ul>

<p>
Technical analysis is widely used for timing entries and exits,
especially in short to medium-term trading.
</p>

<p class="text-muted">
Charts don’t predict the future — they reveal market behavior.
</p>

